
=========================================================================
	How to empty recycle bin in Linux command line
=========================================================================

[Method #1]
Install the tool "trash-cli", then you can use command 
"trash-empty" to empty the trash bin.

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install trash-cli

trash-list
trash-empty
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

[Method #2]
Without installing any tool, you can empty the trash bin by:

rm -rf ~/.local/share/Trash/*
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Prefer using trash-cli (method #1), since after Method #2, 
the icon update to the recycle bin is not correct sometimes.

=========================================================================
	END
=========================================================================

